SET biography = E'Since graduating as an interior designer at ENSAAMA – Olivier de Serres in 1993, Nicolas Aubagnac has been pushing his creativity in different directions. In 1997, his desire to dedicate himself to his work without constraints led him to create his own agency with Delphine Read, presenting a collection of lighting.\n\nIn 2002, he gained international attention for the first time for his exhibit at PAD (Paris Art + Design). Since then, his work has seamlessly blended Art Deco influences with contemporary sensibility. Known initially as an interior and lighting designer, Aubagnac now works across furniture, objects, and interior architecture.\n\n\n\nhttps://res.cloudinary.com/dif1oamtj/image/upload/v1775796551/nicolas-aubagnac-768x1013_qcoxik.jpg | Nicolas Aubagnac | 28% | right\n\nHis pieces are represented by Maison Gerard in New York and Galerie Marcilhac in Paris. He has created special collections for the famous Parisian gallery, designing contemporary furniture in the Art Deco spirit — pedestal tables in bronze and travertine, and refined lighting fixtures that project Art Deco into the future. He has also collaborated with Ateliers Pinton on rug designs.\n\n\n\nhttps://res.cloudinary.com/dif1oamtj/video/upload/v1775796640/VIDEO-Table-des-Alpes-Nicolas-Aubagnac_dah1t9.mp4 | poster:https://res.cloudinary.com/dif1oamtj/image/upload/v1775796973/Alpes-table-basse-4-1024x682_jni5yq.jpg | Collaboration with Fonderie Macheret | | left\n\n\n\nhttps://res.cloudinary.com/dif1oamtj/image/upload/v1775796630/Mobilier-National-Bureau-2_vw6sj1.jpg | Commissioned Desk for the Mobilier National | 28% | right'
